Niger State Governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani Bello, has directed political appointees and other public servants in both state and local government areas of the state aspiring for political offices in 2023 to tender their resignation letters before March 13, 2022. In a statement issued by Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Ahmed Ibrahim Matane, the governor said the recent Electoral Act 2022, signed by President Muhammadu Buhari, provides that political appointees and public servants aspiring to contest elections must resign their positions before the conduct of political party primaries. It stated, “In compliance with this provision, all political appointees and other public servants serving in both state and local governments should submit their letters of resignation to the Office of Secretary to the State Government on or before March 31, 2022. “This is for your information and strict compliance please,” the statement declared.